WEBVTT

00:00:05.214 --> 00:00:10.428
Is the destiny of mankind controlled
by some transcendental entity or Law?

00:00:11.387 --> 00:00:14.390
Is it like the hand of
God hovering above?

00:00:15.433 --> 00:00:17.143
At least it is true...

00:00:17.727 --> 00:00:21.272
...that man has no
control, even over his own will.

00:00:24.400 --> 00:00:28.279
I want to ask you to kill a man for me.

00:00:29.030 --> 00:00:30.114
Kill a man?

00:00:30.281 --> 00:00:30.740
Who?

00:00:31.365 --> 00:00:34.410
The man who is in next
line to the throne of Midland...

00:00:34.577 --> 00:00:35.953
...Count Yurius.

00:00:37.000 --> 00:00:43.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

00:00:57.850 --> 00:00:59.852
<i>Feel no shame about shape.</i>

00:00:59.977 --> 00:01:01.729
<i>Weather changes the phrase.</i>

00:01:01.979 --> 00:01:05.441
<i>Even mother will
show you another way.</i>

00:01:05.691 --> 00:01:07.902
<i>So, put your glasses on.</i>

00:01:08.027 --> 00:01:09.945
<i>Nothing will be wrong.</i>

00:01:10.071 --> 00:01:12.198
<i>There's no blame, there's no fame.</i>

00:01:12.323 --> 00:01:14.033
<i>It's up to you.</i>

00:01:14.200 --> 00:01:17.661
<i>The first words should be found.</i>

00:01:18.329 --> 00:01:21.332
<i>Whatever holds you back.</i>

00:01:22.083 --> 00:01:22.708
<i>I...</i>

00:01:23.084 --> 00:01:23.793
<i>... can...</i>

00:01:23.918 --> 00:01:25.961
<i>I can get it off.</i>

00:01:26.087 --> 00:01:26.962
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:01:27.213 --> 00:01:27.963
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:01:28.089 --> 00:01:29.799
<i>Tell me what you want.</i>

00:01:29.965 --> 00:01:30.966
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:01:31.175 --> 00:01:31.926
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:01:32.093 --> 00:01:33.844
<i>I don't know why you are afraid.</i>

00:01:34.095 --> 00:01:34.970
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:01:35.221 --> 00:01:35.971
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:01:36.222 --> 00:01:37.681
<i>Tell me what you'd say.</i>

00:01:37.973 --> 00:01:38.974
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:01:39.183 --> 00:01:40.101
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:01:40.226 --> 00:01:40.851
<i>Too late...</i>

00:01:41.060 --> 00:01:42.561
<i>It's too late.</i>

00:01:47.608 --> 00:01:51.612
Noble Man

00:02:23.894 --> 00:02:24.812
Yurius...

00:02:25.062 --> 00:02:26.063
I'm in luck.

00:02:29.650 --> 00:02:30.943
Who is that kid?

00:02:40.202 --> 00:02:41.287
Stand up, Adonis!

00:02:41.412 --> 00:02:42.538
How shameful you are!

00:02:42.830 --> 00:02:44.832
Were you really born of royal blood?

00:02:46.333 --> 00:02:47.293
Now stand up!

00:02:47.334 --> 00:02:48.294
Do not rest!

00:02:48.586 --> 00:02:50.838
Your enemy never
lets you rest in battle!

00:02:51.297 --> 00:02:54.091
Your Highness,
kindly call it a day for now...

00:02:54.216 --> 00:02:55.467
Do not disturb us, Hassan!

00:02:56.552 --> 00:02:58.095
Adonis will someday become...

00:02:58.220 --> 00:03:01.348
...commander of the White Dragon
Knights, the strongest troop in the kingdom!

00:03:01.807 --> 00:03:03.100
And that is not all!

00:03:03.601 --> 00:03:08.689
It is even possible that he will
marry Lady Charlotte and rule all Midland!

00:03:09.231 --> 00:03:10.357
Since he was born royal...

00:03:10.482 --> 00:03:13.569
...he must carry such great
responsibilities on his shoulders!

00:03:13.861 --> 00:03:16.238
As a son of royalty,
such a burden is his destiny!

00:03:17.740 --> 00:03:18.490
Fight on!

00:03:18.824 --> 00:03:21.243
Challenge me and
beat me back at least once!

00:03:36.508 --> 00:03:38.135
So much for today.

00:03:41.388 --> 00:03:44.642
Keep yourself warm, and be
ready for tomorrow's training.

00:03:48.771 --> 00:03:49.897
Master Adonis...

00:03:50.272 --> 00:03:52.608
...you're quite injured,
I will treat your wounds.

00:03:53.651 --> 00:03:55.736
Your father is desperate.

00:03:56.028 --> 00:04:00.491
All alone, he has tried to raise
you to maturity as a man and knight.

00:04:01.116 --> 00:04:04.245
You should not think ill of your father.

00:04:36.026 --> 00:04:38.862
Sir Griffith, we have heard your story...

00:04:39.154 --> 00:04:41.907
That you protected the
Princess' life with your own body...

00:04:42.032 --> 00:04:43.367
How courageous you are!

00:04:43.659 --> 00:04:46.787
It is kind of you, but I am
no greater than a coward.

00:04:46.912 --> 00:04:47.913
Sir Griffith.

00:04:49.665 --> 00:04:52.293
Oh, it's Lord Raban and Lord Owen.

00:04:52.668 --> 00:04:55.379
That was a terrible affair
that occurred during the Hunt.

00:04:56.255 --> 00:05:00.551
Indeed, we nearly lost an
important property of Midland's army.

00:05:00.884 --> 00:05:02.303
My life is nothing.

00:05:02.678 --> 00:05:05.389
It is only important that
Princess Charlotte is safe from harm.

00:05:17.443 --> 00:05:20.195
Oh, she has
become even more charming.

00:05:21.280 --> 00:05:23.824
She must be in love with someone.

00:05:28.203 --> 00:05:30.414
Your Highness,
please excuse my tongue.

00:05:30.539 --> 00:05:34.293
However, your rough lessons have
recently taken another turn in that direction.

00:05:34.793 --> 00:05:36.920
I understand what
you're going through...

00:05:37.046 --> 00:05:40.215
...but you should be a little
softer on the Young Master.

00:05:40.466 --> 00:05:41.717
I know.

00:05:42.301 --> 00:05:45.304
Lately, I have had little success
with my duties in the royal court.

00:05:46.055 --> 00:05:49.600
Owing to such affairs,
I have become quite irritated.

00:05:50.351 --> 00:05:53.354
I earnestly beg you not
to overextend yourself.

00:06:30.015 --> 00:06:31.141
Is it the wind?

00:06:39.608 --> 00:06:40.275
What?

00:06:40.401 --> 00:06:41.235
A burglar?

00:07:03.882 --> 00:07:06.260
I-I know you...

00:07:07.010 --> 00:07:08.178
You are...

00:07:08.679 --> 00:07:09.680
...Griffith's...

00:07:21.692 --> 00:07:22.526
Excuse me...

00:07:25.070 --> 00:07:26.447
B-Burglar?

00:07:27.781 --> 00:07:28.532
He saw...

00:07:53.807 --> 00:07:54.933
H-Hey...

00:08:06.987 --> 00:08:08.363
What was that noise?

00:08:08.697 --> 00:08:09.990
What is happening, Your Highness?

00:08:11.450 --> 00:08:13.202
M-Master Adonis!

00:08:13.243 --> 00:08:13.994
Who are you?

00:08:19.750 --> 00:08:20.501
Let's go!

00:08:20.626 --> 00:08:21.627
Burglar!

00:08:21.752 --> 00:08:22.836
Don't let him get away!

00:08:23.629 --> 00:08:24.505
What happened?

00:08:24.630 --> 00:08:25.506
What's all this noise?

00:08:26.340 --> 00:08:28.342
A burglar trespassed
upon His Highness' room!

00:08:28.592 --> 00:08:30.093
I-It can't be!

00:08:33.180 --> 00:08:34.556
Oh, no...

00:08:39.520 --> 00:08:41.563
How merciless this is...

00:08:44.149 --> 00:08:48.403
After all that, this child didn't see his
father's affectionate smile once in his life.

00:08:51.949 --> 00:08:53.033
Mr. Hassan...

00:08:55.327 --> 00:08:56.537
Find the burglar!

00:08:57.329 --> 00:08:59.790
You must not let him
get out of the courtyard alive!

00:08:59.915 --> 00:09:00.457
Yes, sir!

00:09:22.479 --> 00:09:23.605
A sewer...

00:09:23.730 --> 00:09:24.439
Find him!

00:09:24.565 --> 00:09:25.482
He fell through here!

00:09:44.001 --> 00:09:45.002
That sound...

00:09:46.086 --> 00:09:47.504
I hear the sound of...

00:09:48.130 --> 00:09:49.131
...swords in battle...

00:09:54.970 --> 00:09:56.096
Gambino!

00:09:59.266 --> 00:10:00.225
That's right...

00:10:00.726 --> 00:10:04.271
I always desperately
wanted you to appreciate me.

00:10:24.416 --> 00:10:26.543
Stop it!

00:11:16.593 --> 00:11:20.055
I bet Griffith is enjoying a
succulent meal right about now.

00:11:20.430 --> 00:11:23.934
There are a lot of perks that he can
enjoy at the Princess' evening party.

00:11:24.226 --> 00:11:26.311
He has nothing to worry
about but the formalities!

00:11:28.563 --> 00:11:30.982
By the way, where is Guts?

00:11:31.608 --> 00:11:33.485
I haven't seen him since this morning.

00:11:33.735 --> 00:11:37.572
I bet he is busy, practicing
with his sword as always!

00:11:37.948 --> 00:11:39.199
He is just slacking off!

00:11:39.491 --> 00:11:43.870
Our two companies were
supposed to do joint drills today!

00:11:44.121 --> 00:11:46.873
Without giving me any
notice, he never showed!

00:11:47.124 --> 00:11:49.000
No need to get so furious...

00:11:49.126 --> 00:11:51.086
Damn, she's scary!

00:11:58.093 --> 00:11:58.760
Guts!

00:12:00.470 --> 00:12:03.098
Guts, where have you been
running around all day long?

00:12:03.473 --> 00:12:05.517
Thanks to you, we've gotten in trouble!

00:12:06.268 --> 00:12:08.520
Do you really care
about the unity of our band?

00:12:11.022 --> 00:12:12.858
Wait, is this an arrow wound?

00:12:13.775 --> 00:12:14.901
Griffith...

00:12:15.485 --> 00:12:16.778
...where is he?

00:12:17.404 --> 00:12:21.491
Griffith attends the Lady
Charlotte's soiree in Promrose palace.

00:12:21.658 --> 00:12:22.534
I see...

00:12:23.910 --> 00:12:24.661
Hey!

00:12:25.620 --> 00:12:26.872
I still have words for you...

00:12:28.165 --> 00:12:29.666
What's wrong with Guts?

00:12:49.436 --> 00:12:50.687
Griffith...

00:12:57.068 --> 00:12:58.820
I am a little tired...

00:13:05.202 --> 00:13:07.037
Please have a seat here.

00:13:10.707 --> 00:13:11.708
Thank you.

00:13:13.710 --> 00:13:14.586
Wait!

00:13:18.548 --> 00:13:20.592
Are you going there
in that shabby outfit?

00:13:20.967 --> 00:13:22.803
Don't bring shame on Griffith.

00:13:23.470 --> 00:13:26.306
You better wait until they
finish talking if you want to see him!

00:13:28.558 --> 00:13:29.476
I'm borrowing this.

00:13:40.862 --> 00:13:41.947
H-Hey...

00:13:46.117 --> 00:13:51.998
Truth be told, I do not like holding a
soiree, it is only a clamorous imposition.

00:13:52.999 --> 00:13:59.339
This soiree is being held to comfort
those who have restlessly fought in battles.

00:13:59.756 --> 00:14:00.507
But...

00:14:00.882 --> 00:14:03.009
I think they should rather...

00:14:03.718 --> 00:14:07.013
...stop the war itself
than hold a soiree like this one.

00:14:07.889 --> 00:14:11.351
Why do most men commit
themselves to the affair of bloodshed?

00:14:11.893 --> 00:14:14.396
You asked me such on
the hunting field, My Lady.

00:14:14.771 --> 00:14:16.231
Oh, yes...

00:14:17.148 --> 00:14:22.404
Indeed, a man may have a
barbarous side as you indicate.

00:14:23.029 --> 00:14:24.030
However, that is...

00:14:24.489 --> 00:14:27.409
...a double-edged sword that can be
used as a tool for winning precious things...

00:14:27.784 --> 00:14:29.369
...as well as protecting them.

00:14:29.786 --> 00:14:30.996
Precious things?

00:14:31.162 --> 00:14:33.248
Such as family and lovers?

00:14:34.040 --> 00:14:35.792
For some of men,
such things are duly precious.

00:14:37.544 --> 00:14:43.300
But I believe that a man can find
another, more precious thing, before those...

00:14:47.429 --> 00:14:51.933
Something one pursues for one's own
sake, and not for the sake of any other.

00:14:52.058 --> 00:14:53.059
A dream.

00:14:53.810 --> 00:14:54.811
A dream...

00:14:57.647 --> 00:14:59.649
A dream can hold
supremacy over the world...

00:15:00.692 --> 00:15:03.194
...for one who
dedicates his entire life to forging...

00:15:03.320 --> 00:15:04.905
...only a single sword.

00:15:05.572 --> 00:15:07.824
While many dreams
can be pursued in solitude...

00:15:08.033 --> 00:15:08.950
...some dreams are...

00:15:09.159 --> 00:15:12.412
...like storms, blowing apart hundreds
or thousands of other dreams as they go.

00:15:13.038 --> 00:15:15.457
A dream can support a
man's life or make him suffer...

00:15:15.832 --> 00:15:18.460
A dream can make a man
feel alive, and kill him as well.

00:15:18.960 --> 00:15:21.171
Even if a man is
abandoned by that dream...

00:15:21.296 --> 00:15:23.798
...part of it will remain to
smolder deep within his heart.

00:15:25.300 --> 00:15:28.970
Every man should visualize his
own life in this way, at least once.

00:15:29.429 --> 00:15:32.933
Living as a martyr for
God in the name of a dream...

00:15:35.435 --> 00:15:38.480
Some say there's nothing more
to life than to live long and die in vain.

00:15:39.189 --> 00:15:42.233
I hate that sort of
notion, I can't stand it.

00:15:47.614 --> 00:15:50.367
I am sorry, I became
carried away with my talk.

00:15:50.825 --> 00:15:53.370
You must be getting bored.

00:15:53.745 --> 00:15:55.372
O-Oh, no...

00:15:56.873 --> 00:16:01.628
I have never talked
with a man like this before...

00:16:02.253 --> 00:16:07.258
I thought you were one of the aristocracy
when first I laid my eyes upon you.

00:16:07.884 --> 00:16:10.637
Young as you are,
you have so much presence.

00:16:11.388 --> 00:16:16.142
But when you taught me how to
play a piece of reed in the hunting field...

00:16:16.351 --> 00:16:17.352
...you looked...

00:16:18.269 --> 00:16:19.896
...like a child.

00:16:21.272 --> 00:16:25.986
And now, you are like a
philosopher telling me your thoughts.

00:16:28.029 --> 00:16:29.489
You are marvelous...

00:16:36.913 --> 00:16:41.543
Your friends must be
fascinated by your charm, too.

00:16:43.169 --> 00:16:45.422
They are my able soldiers.

00:16:45.922 --> 00:16:51.177
They are important comrades
who devote themselves to my dream.

00:16:52.387 --> 00:16:55.015
However, they are
not necessarily my friends.

00:16:56.391 --> 00:17:01.438
It is my perception that a true
friend never relies on another's dream.

00:17:02.063 --> 00:17:04.190
A person with the potential...

00:17:04.441 --> 00:17:07.902
...to be my true friend must be able to
find his reason for life without my help.

00:17:08.611 --> 00:17:14.659
And, he would have to put his heart
and soul into protecting his dream.

00:17:15.285 --> 00:17:18.621
He would never hesitate to
fight for his dream, even against me.

00:17:19.789 --> 00:17:21.499
For me, a true friend is...

00:17:22.042 --> 00:17:24.794
...one who stands
equal on those terms.

00:17:37.557 --> 00:17:39.559
You have great confidence in yourself.

00:17:42.270 --> 00:17:45.148
I have attained
everything with my faith.

00:17:46.024 --> 00:17:47.067
And now...

00:17:48.151 --> 00:17:52.530
I am allowed to talk with you,
the Princess of the kingdom.

00:17:54.449 --> 00:17:56.534
Will you tell me your dream?

00:17:57.410 --> 00:17:58.661
Princess!

00:17:59.704 --> 00:18:01.331
Something awful has happened!

00:18:02.082 --> 00:18:03.166
What ever is the matter?

00:18:03.291 --> 00:18:06.336
Your uncle, Count
Yurius, has been killed!

00:18:06.669 --> 00:18:07.670
That can not be!

00:18:07.796 --> 00:18:08.588
He was assassinated!

00:18:08.713 --> 00:18:12.217
A burglar stole into his study and
even Young Master Adonis was killed...

00:18:13.093 --> 00:18:15.095
The court has been
thrown into an uproar.

00:18:34.697 --> 00:18:36.199
What tremendous numbers...

00:18:36.324 --> 00:18:40.203
Well, I've heard that the
upcoming battles could end the war.

00:18:40.870 --> 00:18:42.747
I hope such a thing becomes reality.

00:18:42.831 --> 00:18:43.832
No need to worry!

00:18:43.957 --> 00:18:46.751
Midland's army has a guardian angel!

00:18:49.712 --> 00:18:50.964
Speak of the devil...

00:19:01.474 --> 00:19:03.476
Are you setting out?

00:19:06.604 --> 00:19:08.273
Yes, Minister Foss.

00:19:08.523 --> 00:19:10.900
We no longer have
General Yurius, only you are left.

00:19:11.401 --> 00:19:15.864
You are now the guardian deity of
Midland, I prey for your good fortune...

00:19:16.364 --> 00:19:17.532
...in battle.

00:19:17.907 --> 00:19:20.034
That seems to be an exaggeration.

00:19:20.493 --> 00:19:22.787
However, I shall
exert myself to the utmost.

00:19:22.912 --> 00:19:28.793
At any rate, I cannot bear
this news of the assassinations.

00:19:29.169 --> 00:19:34.174
It is cruel that Young Master
Adonis was killed, he was only a child.

00:19:34.382 --> 00:19:36.759
Only a devil would do that.

00:19:36.885 --> 00:19:38.928
No, it was not a devil's doing.

00:19:40.305 --> 00:19:42.140
It was a man's doing, Minister.

00:19:45.268 --> 00:19:49.564
By the way Sir Griffith,
I happened to hear of an odd rumor.

00:19:49.814 --> 00:19:51.024
An odd rumor?

00:19:51.191 --> 00:19:54.068
That the arrow aimed at
Lady Charlotte in the hunting field...

00:19:54.277 --> 00:19:57.447
...could possibly
have been aimed at you.

00:19:58.072 --> 00:19:59.199
Could that be true?

00:19:59.324 --> 00:20:01.701
Aiming at a humble unit commander?

00:20:01.910 --> 00:20:03.578
According to the rumor...

00:20:03.703 --> 00:20:09.459
...the assassin did not hail from the
Empire of Chuder, but our own court.

00:20:10.084 --> 00:20:11.836
In the royal court, there is...

00:20:11.961 --> 00:20:14.589
...a cavern filled with evil spirits
buried under its beautiful surface.

00:20:14.714 --> 00:20:19.344
It is no surprise that many people
are brewing up dark plots in the court.

00:20:19.719 --> 00:20:20.553
My goodness...

00:20:20.845 --> 00:20:22.347
It does not matter at all...

00:20:22.472 --> 00:20:26.226
...whether they kill a man within the
sanctuary of the court or outside of it.

00:20:26.351 --> 00:20:28.603
As far as such people are concerned...

00:20:28.978 --> 00:20:30.730
That is an interesting theory.

00:20:31.231 --> 00:20:32.565
Well, then I will...

00:20:32.857 --> 00:20:35.485
...strive to keep any unpleasantries
as far outside the court as possible.

00:20:35.985 --> 00:20:36.861
Excuse me.

00:20:39.822 --> 00:20:42.242
He seems to have held
himself far above our conversation.

00:20:42.367 --> 00:20:44.744
Was it not his doing?

00:20:47.121 --> 00:20:48.623
No, that cannot be true.

00:20:48.748 --> 00:20:51.125
If it was an accident,
it would be far too good to be true.

00:20:53.503 --> 00:20:56.339
W-Wait, could it be
that he knows about me?

00:20:58.007 --> 00:21:01.094
No, no man could discover
my intrigue, however keen he is.

00:21:01.219 --> 00:21:03.388
Besides, there is no evidence left.

00:21:27.870 --> 00:21:29.789
For me, a true friend is...

00:21:30.164 --> 00:21:32.792
...one who stands
equal on those terms.

00:22:02.655 --> 00:22:04.782
<i>Looking back, the morning comes.</i>

00:22:04.949 --> 00:22:08.453
<i>Don't find your face in your glass.</i>

00:22:09.662 --> 00:22:12.457
<i>Take the moonlight by the tail.</i>

00:22:12.582 --> 00:22:15.460
<i>It's a rainy sight that you're shading.</i>

00:22:17.170 --> 00:22:18.713
<i>What is that?</i>

00:22:18.838 --> 00:22:19.964
<i>It's just the same.</i>

00:22:20.089 --> 00:22:23.176
<i>What is trying on your crown?</i>

00:22:24.427 --> 00:22:27.305
<i>I'm spending my
glass and walking back.</i>

00:22:27.430 --> 00:22:30.600
<i>So wear my glass, you're fading.</i>

00:22:30.975 --> 00:22:34.228
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:34.729 --> 00:22:37.607
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

